The gut is responsible for absorbing nutrients from the food we eat, which are necessary for hormone production. Nutrient deficiencies such as low magnesium and low vitamin D can lead to hormonal imbalance. For instance, low levels of vitamin D have been linked to decreased levels of testosterone in men. Additionally, nutrient deficiencies can also lead to an increase in stress hormones such as cortisol, which can then further exacerbate hormonal imbalances. This is a reminder, if you're trying to balance your hormones, make sure your healthcare professional is also addressing your gut health. It's also looking into mold, toxicity, heavy metals, your lifestyle. This is all very important.
